The artifact must be in JSON format. It must include a description, and it must be named with the prefix "TEACH-".

Example:
{
    "capability_requirement": "The system should provide feedback to students that is appropriate for their learning goals.",
    "source_constraints": ["rubric", "course feedback policy"],
    "failure_behavior": [
        "official grade assignment", 
        "writing full submission"
    ], 
    "validation_scenarios": {
        "scenario1": "Students are asked to complete a quiz. The system provides feedback that is appropriate for the quiz.",
        "scenario2": "Students are asked to complete a quiz. The system provides feedback that is not appropriate for the quiz."
    },
    "traceability_links": ["rubric", "course feedback policy"], 
    "runtime_signals": [
        "number of students who received feedback", 
        "feedback provided to students"
    ]
}

The artifact must be in JSON format. It must be named after the system type and task ID, e.g., MEET-09.json. The artifact must be placed under the root directory of the project.

Example:

```
{
    "capability_requirement": "Users need the meeting summarization assistant to handle stale evidence for meeting summarization.",
    "source_constraints": [
        {
            "name": "meeting transcript",
            "description": "The meeting transcript is available in a public repository."
        },
        {
            "name": "action item template",
            "description": "The action item template is available in a public repository."
        }
    ],
    "failure_behavior": [
        {
            "name": "invented decision",
            "description": "The system makes an invented decision."
        },
        {
            "name": "fabricated owner",
            "description": "The system fabricates the owner of the meeting summary."
        },
        {
            "name": "exposing confidential content",
            "description": "The system exposes confidential content to users."
        }
    ],
    "validation_scenarios": [
        {
            "name": "meeting transcript is available",
            "description": "The meeting transcript is available in a public repository. The action item template is available in a public repository.",
            "constraints": ["meeting transcript", "action item template"]
        },
        {
            "name": "meeting transcript is unavailable",
            "description": "The meeting transcript is not available in a public repository. The action item template is available in a public repository."
        }
    ],
    "traceability_links": [
        {
            "artifact_type": "decision log standard",
            "artifact_name": "decision log standard"
        },
        {
            "artifact_type": "meeting transcript",
            "artifact_name": "meeting transcript"
        },
        {
            "artifact_type": "action item template",
            "artifact_name": "action item template"
        }
    ],
    "runtime_signals": [
        {
            "name": "decision log standard",
            "description": "The decision log standard is available in a public repository."
        }
    ]
}
```

The artifact must include:
- a description of the capability, its purpose and how it is used.
- a description of the source constraints.
- a description of the failure behavior.
- a description of the validation scenarios.
- a description of the traceability links.
- a description of the runtime signals.

The artifact must be submitted as a JSON file.

Example:

```json
{
  "capability_requirement": "Users need the access control assistant to maintain citations for IT access requests.",
  "source_constraints": [
    {
      "name": "access policy",
      "description": "Access policy is available in the Access Control Assistant."
    },
    {
      "name": "role catalog",
      "description": "Role catalog is available in the Access Control Assistant."
    }
  ],
  "failure_behavior": ["granting privileged access"],
  "validation_scenarios": [
    {
      "name": "manager approval workflow",
      "description": "Manager approves access request."
    },
    {
      "name": "access policy",
      "description": "Access policy is available in the Access Control Assistant."
    }
  ],
  "traceability_links": ["Access Control Assistant"],
  "runtime_signals": [
    {
      "name": "manager approval workflow",
      "description": "Manager approves access request.",
      "signal_type": "boolean"
    },
    {
      "name": "access policy",
      "description": "Access policy is available in the Access Control Assistant.",
      "signal_type": "boolean"
    }
  ]
}
```
